   {
      "body" : "Concept ACK. OK with either policy rule or consensus rule, finalized LN bitcoin scripts will be compatible.\r\n\r\nTo echo jl2012 's comment about having UTXOs, policy rules to an eventual SF is complicated because doing something as simple as ```OP_DUP \r\nOP_IF OP_SHA256 <PUSHDATA> OP_EQUAL```\r\ncan invalidate scripts (you're computing on the same data in two places, one of which would be constrained in the SF when activated and the other constrained in the script itself). It is theoretically plausible to construct this kind of script for an actual useful purpose (e.g. if OP_FALSE as input, the other branch would compute on the next item on the stack, albeit it may be possible to construct those scripts more optimally without this problem in the first place, the possibility that it can happen with some kind of script is a concern).",
      "created_at" : "2016-09-01T23:59:08Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/8526#issuecomment-244247547",
